{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Well, this is 2009."},{"time":5000,"text":"And it's the Bicentenary of Charles Darwin."},{"time":10000,"text":"And all over the world, eminent evolutionists"},{"time":13000,"text":"are anxious to celebrate this."},{"time":15000,"text":"And what they're planning to do is to enlighten us"},{"time":19000,"text":"on almost every aspect"},{"time":21000,"text":"of Darwin and his life,"},{"time":23000,"text":"and how he changed our thinking."},{"time":25000,"text":"I say almost every aspect,"},{"time":28000,"text":"because there is one aspect of this story"},{"time":31000,"text":"which they have thrown no light on."},{"time":34000,"text":"And they seem anxious to skirt around it and step over it"},{"time":37000,"text":"and to talk about something else."},{"time":39000,"text":"So I'm going to talk about it."},{"time":41000,"text":"It's the question of, why are we so different from the chimpanzees?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":47000,"text":"We get the geneticists keeping on telling us"},{"time":49000,"text":"how extremely closely we are related -- hardly any genes of difference,"},{"time":53000,"text":"very, very closely related."},{"time":56000,"text":"And yet, when you look at the phenotypes,"},{"time":59000,"text":"there's a chimp, there's a man;"},{"time":61000,"text":"they're astoundingly different,"},{"time":63000,"text":"no resemblance at all."},{"time":65000,"text":"I'm not talking about airy-fairy stuff"},{"time":67000,"text":"about culture or psychology, or behavior."},{"time":71000,"text":"I'm talking about ground-base, nitty-gritty,"},{"time":74000,"text":"measurable physical differences."},{"time":76000,"text":"They, that one,"},{"time":78000,"text":"is hairy and walking on four legs."},{"time":80000,"text":"That one is a naked biped. Why?"},{"time":84000,"text":"I mean --"},{"time":86000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":87000,"text":"if I'm a good Darwinist, I've got to believe"},{"time":89000,"text":"there's a reason for that."},{"time":91000,"text":"If we changed so much, something must have happened."},{"time":94000,"text":"What happened?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":96000,"text":"Now 50 years ago, that was a laughably simple question."},{"time":99000,"text":"Everybody knew the answer."},{"time":101000,"text":"They knew what happened."},{"time":103000,"text":"The ancestor of the apes stayed in the trees;"},{"time":105000,"text":"our ancestors went out onto the plain."},{"time":108000,"text":"That explained everything."},{"time":111000,"text":"We had to get up on our legs to peer over the tall grass,"},{"time":114000,"text":"or to chase after animals,"},{"time":116000,"text":"or to free our hands for weapons."},{"time":118000,"text":"And we got so overheated in the chase"},{"time":122000,"text":"that we had to take off that fur coat and throw it away."},{"time":126000,"text":"Everybody knew that, for generations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129000,"text":"But then, in the '90s, something began to unravel."},{"time":133000,"text":"The paleontologists themselves looked a bit more closely"},{"time":137000,"text":"at the accompanying microfauna"},{"time":141000,"text":"that lived in the same time and place as the hominids."},{"time":145000,"text":"And they weren't savanna species."},{"time":148000,"text":"And they looked at the herbivores. And they weren't savanna herbivores."},{"time":152000,"text":"And then they were so clever, they found a way to analyze"},{"time":155000,"text":"fossilized pollen."},{"time":157000,"text":"Shock, horror."},{"time":159000,"text":"The fossilized pollen was not of savanna vegetation."},{"time":164000,"text":"Some of it even came from lianas,"},{"time":166000,"text":"those things that dangle in the middle of the jungle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":169000,"text":"So we're left with a situation where"},{"time":171000,"text":"we know that our earliest ancestors"},{"time":175000,"text":"were moving around on four legs in the trees,"},{"time":179000,"text":"before the savanna ecosystem even came into existence."},{"time":184000,"text":"This is not something I've made up."},{"time":187000,"text":"It's not a minority theory."},{"time":189000,"text":"Everybody agrees with it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":191000,"text":"Professor Tobias came over from South Africa"},{"time":195000,"text":"and spoke to University College London."},{"time":198000,"text":"He said, \"Everything I've been telling you for the last 20 years,"},{"time":201000,"text":"forget about it. It was wrong."},{"time":204000,"text":"We've got to go back to square one and start again.\""},{"time":208000,"text":"It made him very unpopular. They didn't want to go back to square one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":214000,"text":"I mean, it's a terrible thing to happen."},{"time":216000,"text":"You've got this beautiful paradigm."},{"time":219000,"text":"You've believed it through generations."},{"time":221000,"text":"Nobody has questioned it."},{"time":223000,"text":"You've been constructing fanciful things on top of it,"},{"time":227000,"text":"relying on it to be as solid as a rock."},{"time":229000,"text":"And now it's whipped away from under you."},{"time":232000,"text":"What do you do? What does a scientist do in that case?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":235000,"text":"Well, we know the answer because"},{"time":237000,"text":"Thomas S. Kuhn"},{"time":240000,"text":"wrote a seminal treatise"},{"time":244000,"text":"about this back in 1962."},{"time":246000,"text":"He said what scientists do"},{"time":248000,"text":"when a paradigm fails"},{"time":252000,"text":"is, guess what -- they carry on as if nothing had happened."},{"time":255000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":258000,"text":"If they haven't got a paradigm they can't ask the question."},{"time":261000,"text":"So they say, \"Yes it's wrong,"},{"time":263000,"text":"but supposing it was right ...\""},{"time":265000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":267000,"text":"And the only other option open to them"},{"time":271000,"text":"is to stop asking the questions."},{"time":273000,"text":"So that is what they have done now."},{"time":277000,"text":"That's why you don't hear them talking about it. It's yesterday's question."}]},{"cues":[{"time":280000,"text":"Some of them have even elevated it into a principle."},{"time":283000,"text":"It's what we ought to be doing."},{"time":285000,"text":"Aaron Filler from Harvard said,"},{"time":288000,"text":"\"Isn't it time we stopped talking about selective pressures?"},{"time":292000,"text":"I mean, why don't we talk about, well, there's chromosomes, and there's genes."},{"time":295000,"text":"And we just record what we see.\""},{"time":298000,"text":"Charles Darwin must be spinning in his grave!"},{"time":301000,"text":"He knew all about that kind of science."},{"time":304000,"text":"And he called it hypothesis-free science."},{"time":307000,"text":"And he despised it from the bottom of his heart."},{"time":310000,"text":"And if you're going to say,"},{"time":313000,"text":"\"I'm going to stop talking about selective pressures,\""},{"time":315000,"text":"you can take \"The Origin of Species\" and throw it out of the window,"},{"time":319000,"text":"for it's about nothing else but selective pressures."}]},{"cues":[{"time":321000,"text":"And the irony of it is,"},{"time":323000,"text":"that this is one occasion of a paradigm collapse"},{"time":326000,"text":"where we didn't have to wait for a new paradigm to come up."},{"time":330000,"text":"There was one waiting in the wings."},{"time":332000,"text":"It had been waiting there since 1960"},{"time":334000,"text":"when Alister Hardy, a marine biologist,"},{"time":337000,"text":"said, \"I think what happened,"},{"time":339000,"text":"perhaps our ancestors"},{"time":341000,"text":"had a more aquatic existence"},{"time":343000,"text":"for some of the time.\""},{"time":346000,"text":"He kept it to himself for 30 years."},{"time":348000,"text":"But then the press got hold of it and all hell broke loose."},{"time":351000,"text":"All his colleagues said, \"This is outrageous."},{"time":354000,"text":"You've exposed us to public ridicule!"},{"time":358000,"text":"You must never do that again.\""},{"time":360000,"text":"And at that time, it became set in stone:"},{"time":363000,"text":"the aquatic theory should be dumped"},{"time":366000,"text":"with the UFOs and the yetis,"},{"time":368000,"text":"as part of the lunatic fringe of science."}]},{"cues":[{"time":372000,"text":"Well I don't think that."},{"time":374000,"text":"I think that Hardy had a lot going for him."},{"time":376000,"text":"I'd like to talk about just a handful"},{"time":379000,"text":"of what have been called the"},{"time":381000,"text":"hallmarks of mankind,"},{"time":383000,"text":"the things that made us different from everybody else,"},{"time":385000,"text":"and all our relatives."},{"time":387000,"text":"Let's look at our naked skin."},{"time":391000,"text":"It's obvious that most of the things we think about"},{"time":395000,"text":"that have lost their body hair, mammals without body hair,"},{"time":398000,"text":"are aquatic ones, like the dugong, the walrus,"},{"time":401000,"text":"the dolphin, the hippopotamus, the manatee."},{"time":405000,"text":"And a couple of wallowers-in-mud like the babirusa."},{"time":411000,"text":"And you're tempted to think, well perhaps,"},{"time":413000,"text":"could that be why we are naked?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":416000,"text":"I suggested it and people said, \"No no no."},{"time":418000,"text":"I mean, look at the elephant."},{"time":420000,"text":"You've forgotten all about the elephant haven't you?\""},{"time":422000,"text":"So back in 1982 I said,"},{"time":425000,"text":"\"Well perhaps the elephant had an aquatic ancestor.\""},{"time":428000,"text":"Peals of merry laughter!"},{"time":431000,"text":"\"That crazy woman. She's off again. She'll say anything won't she?\""},{"time":434000,"text":"But by now, everybody agrees that the elephant had an aquatic ancestor."},{"time":440000,"text":"This has come 'round to be that all those naked pachyderms"},{"time":443000,"text":"have aquatic ancestors."},{"time":445000,"text":"The last exception was supposed to be the rhinoceros."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447000,"text":"Last year in Florida they found extinct ancestor of a rhinoceros"},{"time":451000,"text":"and said, \"Seems to have spent most of its time in the water.\""},{"time":455000,"text":"So this is a close connection between nakedness and water."},{"time":460000,"text":"As an absolute connection, it only works one way."},{"time":463000,"text":"You can't say all aquatic animals are naked,"},{"time":467000,"text":"because look at the sea otter."},{"time":469000,"text":"But you can say"},{"time":471000,"text":"that every animal that has become naked"},{"time":475000,"text":"has been conditioned by water, in its own lifetime,"},{"time":478000,"text":"or the lifetime of its ancestors. I think this is significant."},{"time":482000,"text":"The only exception is the naked Somalian mole-rat,"},{"time":486000,"text":"which never puts its nose above the surface of the ground."}]},{"cues":[{"time":490000,"text":"And take bipedality."},{"time":492000,"text":"Here you can't find anybody to compare it with,"},{"time":495000,"text":"because we're the only animal that walks upright on two legs."},{"time":500000,"text":"But you can say this: all the apes and all the monkeys"},{"time":503000,"text":"are capable of walking on two legs,"},{"time":505000,"text":"if they want to, for a short time."},{"time":507000,"text":"There is only one circumstance in which they"},{"time":510000,"text":"always, all of them, walk on two legs,"},{"time":513000,"text":"and that is when they are wading through water."},{"time":516000,"text":"Do you think that's significant?"},{"time":518000,"text":"David Attenborough thinks it's significant,"},{"time":520000,"text":"as the possible beginning of our bipedalism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":524000,"text":"Look at the fat layer."},{"time":526000,"text":"We have got, under our skin, a layer of fat, all over:"},{"time":530000,"text":"nothing in the least like that in any other primate."},{"time":534000,"text":"Why should it be there?"},{"time":536000,"text":"Well they do know, that if you look at other aquatic mammals,"},{"time":539000,"text":"the fat that in most land mammals"},{"time":541000,"text":"is deposited inside the body wall,"},{"time":544000,"text":"around the kidneys and the intestines and so on,"},{"time":548000,"text":"has started to migrate to the outside,"},{"time":550000,"text":"and spread out in a layer inside the skin."},{"time":554000,"text":"In the whale it's complete:"},{"time":556000,"text":"no fat inside at all, all in blubber outside."},{"time":559000,"text":"We cannot avoid the suspicion"},{"time":562000,"text":"that in our case it's started to happen."},{"time":565000,"text":"We have got skin lined with this layer."},{"time":569000,"text":"It's the only possible explanation of why humans,"},{"time":572000,"text":"if they're very unlucky,"},{"time":575000,"text":"can become grossly obese,"},{"time":578000,"text":"in a way that would be totally impossible for any other primate, physically impossible."},{"time":582000,"text":"Something very odd, matter-of-factly, never explained."}]},{"cues":[{"time":586000,"text":"The question of why we can speak."},{"time":588000,"text":"We can speak."},{"time":590000,"text":"And the gorilla can't speak. Why?"},{"time":593000,"text":"Nothing to do with his teeth or his tongue or his lungs or anything like that --"},{"time":597000,"text":"purely has to do with its conscious control of its breath."},{"time":602000,"text":"You can't even train a gorilla to say \"Ah\" on request."},{"time":607000,"text":"The only creatures that have got conscious control of their breath"},{"time":612000,"text":"are the diving animals and the diving birds."},{"time":615000,"text":"It was an absolute precondition for our being able to speak."}]},{"cues":[{"time":620000,"text":"And then again, there is the fact that we are streamlined."},{"time":624000,"text":"Trying to imagine a diver"},{"time":626000,"text":"diving into water -- hardly makes a splash."},{"time":628000,"text":"Try to imagine a gorilla"},{"time":631000,"text":"performing the same maneuver,"},{"time":634000,"text":"and you can see that, compared with gorilla,"},{"time":636000,"text":"we are halfway to being shaped like a fish."},{"time":639000,"text":"I am trying to suggest that, for 40-odd years,"},{"time":642000,"text":"this aquatic idea has been miscategorized as lunatic fringe,"},{"time":647000,"text":"and it is not lunatic fringe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":650000,"text":"And the ironic thing about it is that"},{"time":653000,"text":"they are not staving off the aquatic theory"},{"time":656000,"text":"to protect a theory of their own,"},{"time":658000,"text":"which they've all agreed on, and they love."},{"time":660000,"text":"There is nothing there."},{"time":662000,"text":"They are staving off the aquatic theory"},{"time":664000,"text":"to protect a vacuum."},{"time":666000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":669000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":674000,"text":"How do they react when I say these things?"},{"time":677000,"text":"One very common reaction I've heard about 20 times"},{"time":681000,"text":"is, \"But it was investigated."},{"time":683000,"text":"They conducted a serious investigation of this at the beginning,"},{"time":687000,"text":"when Hardy put forward his article.\""},{"time":691000,"text":"I don't believe it."},{"time":694000,"text":"For 35 years I've been looking for any evidence"},{"time":697000,"text":"of any incident of that kind,"},{"time":699000,"text":"and I've concluded that that's one of the urban myths."},{"time":702000,"text":"It's never been done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":705000,"text":"I ask people sometimes, and they say,"},{"time":707000,"text":"\"I like the aquatic theory!"},{"time":709000,"text":"Everybody likes the aquatic theory."},{"time":711000,"text":"Of course they don't believe it, but they like it.\""},{"time":713000,"text":"Well I say, \"Why do you think it's rubbish?\""},{"time":717000,"text":"They say \"Well ..."},{"time":719000,"text":"everybody I talk to says it's rubbish."},{"time":722000,"text":"And they can't all be wrong, can they?\""},{"time":724000,"text":"The answer to that, loud and clear, is, \"Yes! They can all be wrong.\""},{"time":728000,"text":"History is strewn with the cases when they've all got it wrong."},{"time":732000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":740000,"text":"And if you've got a scientific problem like that,"},{"time":742000,"text":"you can't solve it by holding a head count,"},{"time":745000,"text":"and saying, \"More of us say yes than say no.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":748000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":749000,"text":"Apart from that, some of the heads count more than others."},{"time":753000,"text":"Some of them have come over."},{"time":756000,"text":"There was Professor Tobias. He's come over."},{"time":759000,"text":"Daniel Dennett, he's come over."},{"time":761000,"text":"Sir David Attenborough, he's come over."},{"time":765000,"text":"Anybody else out there? Come on in."},{"time":767000,"text":"The water is lovely."}]},{"cues":[{"time":769000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":772000,"text":"And now we've got to look to the future."},{"time":777000,"text":"Ultimately one of three things is going to happen."},{"time":781000,"text":"Either they will go on for the next 40 years, 50 years, 60 years."},{"time":786000,"text":"\"Yeah well we don't talk about that. Let's talk about something interesting.\""},{"time":790000,"text":"That would be very sad."},{"time":792000,"text":"The second thing that could happen"},{"time":794000,"text":"is that some young genius will arrive,"},{"time":796000,"text":"and say, \"I've found it."},{"time":798000,"text":"It was not the savanna, it was not the water, it was this!\""},{"time":802000,"text":"No sign of that happening either."},{"time":805000,"text":"I don't think there is a third option."}]},{"cues":[{"time":807000,"text":"So the third thing that might happen is"},{"time":810000,"text":"a very beautiful thing."},{"time":813000,"text":"If you look back at the early years of the last century,"},{"time":816000,"text":"there was a stand-off, a lot of bickering and bad feeling"},{"time":820000,"text":"between the believers in Mendel,"},{"time":822000,"text":"and the believers in Darwin."},{"time":825000,"text":"It ended with a new synthesis:"},{"time":828000,"text":"Darwin's ideas and Mendel's ideas"},{"time":831000,"text":"blending together."},{"time":833000,"text":"And I think the same thing will happen here."},{"time":836000,"text":"You'll get a new synthesis."},{"time":839000,"text":"Hardy's ideas and Darwin's ideas"},{"time":841000,"text":"will be blended together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":843000,"text":"And we can move forward from there,"},{"time":845000,"text":"and really get somewhere."},{"time":847000,"text":"That would be a beautiful thing."},{"time":850000,"text":"It would be very nice for me if it happened soon."},{"time":853000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":864000,"text":"Because I'm older now than George Burns was when he said,"},{"time":869000,"text":"\"At my age, I don't even buy green bananas.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":873000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":879000,"text":"So if it's going to come and it's going to happen,"},{"time":882000,"text":"what's holding it up?"},{"time":884000,"text":"I can tell you that in three words."},{"time":887000,"text":"Academia says no."},{"time":891000,"text":"They decided in 1960,"},{"time":893000,"text":"\"That belongs with the UFOs and the yetis.\""},{"time":896000,"text":"And it's not easy to change their minds."},{"time":900000,"text":"The professional journals"},{"time":902000,"text":"won't touch it with a barge pole."},{"time":904000,"text":"The textbooks don't mention it."},{"time":907000,"text":"The syllabus doesn't mention even the fact that we're naked,"},{"time":910000,"text":"let alone look for a reason to it."},{"time":913000,"text":"\"Horizon,\" which takes its cue from the academics,"},{"time":916000,"text":"won't touch it with a barge pole."},{"time":918000,"text":"So we never hear the case put for it,"},{"time":922000,"text":"except in jocular references"},{"time":925000,"text":"to people on the lunatic fringe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":927000,"text":"I don't know quite where this diktat comes from."},{"time":933000,"text":"Somebody up there"},{"time":935000,"text":"is issuing the commandment,"},{"time":939000,"text":"\"Thou shalt not believe in the aquatic theory."},{"time":943000,"text":"And if you hope to make progress in this profession,"},{"time":946000,"text":"and you do believe it, you'd better keep it to yourself,"},{"time":950000,"text":"because it will get in your way.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":952000,"text":"So I get the impression that some parts"},{"time":955000,"text":"of the scientific establishment"},{"time":958000,"text":"are morphing into a kind of priesthood."},{"time":962000,"text":"But you know, that makes me feel good,"},{"time":966000,"text":"because Richard Dawkins has told us"},{"time":969000,"text":"how to treat a priesthood."},{"time":971000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":973000,"text":"He says, \"Firstly, you've got to refuse to give it"},{"time":976000,"text":"all the excessive awe and reverence"},{"time":979000,"text":"it's been trained to receive.\""},{"time":981000,"text":"Right. I'll go ahead with that."},{"time":983000,"text":"And secondly, he says,"},{"time":985000,"text":"\"You must never be afraid to rock the boat.\""},{"time":988000,"text":"I'll go along with that too."},{"time":990000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":992000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}